description: Mr. Lodge may be the richest man in Riverdale, but he faces one major problem that could change that -- his own daughter! Veronica's credit cards are the solution to everything, and she's got her Daddykins wrapped around her little finger. When he does put her in her place, though, it's on an epic scale! Will this Daddy/Daughter duo get along without driving each other crazy? Or will Archie drive them both crazy first? Find out in this 100-page digital exclusive!

description:
The Devastator is the geek comedy book series featuring new works by 30+ writers and artists from The Daily Show, The Onion, Adult Swim, Marvel and more!

The Devastator: Apocalypse drops the big one on pop culture's obsession with doomsday. Crawling out of the wreckage are parodies of H.P. Lovecraft, Planet of the Apes, Escape From New York, The Road and more! Featuring contributions from Paul Scheer, Joe Lo Truglio, Danny Hellman, Jordan Morris, and an explosive cover by Michael DeForge. Flip the book around for Oh, the Flesh You Will Eat!, an infectious Dr. Seuss spoof that shows an epidemic from the virus' point-of-view.

Contents

  • The Raw Spiel with the Editor-in-Chief
  • Dinostrodamus by Orpheus Collar
  • Stat Attack - Doomsday Preppers by Amanda Meadows
  • The Craigslist by Lesley Tsina, art by Nate Pride
  • Escape from Raleigh by Patrick Baker, art by Marcie LaCerte
  • Ameripocalypse by Geoffrey Golden, feat. Paul Scheer, photos by Lynne Donahue
  • Cathair Apocalypse by Scott Gross
  • The Bionic Claim by Micki Grover, art by Matt Taylor
  • The All New Horsemen of the Apocalypse by Asterios Kokkinos, art by Rory Midhani
  • Trash is King by Lynne Donahue, feat. Joe Lo Truglio
  • Ameripocalypse II by Geoffrey Golden, feat. Paul Scheer, photos by Lynne Donahue
  • MTV's Cormac McCarthy's The Road Rules by John Ford
  • It's the End of the World as You Want It by Marly Halpern-Graser art by Jojo Ramos
  • Movin' Outland by Jordan Morris, art by Jimmy Hasse
  • The Cosplay After Tomorrow by Danny Hellman
  • A Very Special Epidemic by Mike Betette
  • Union Buster by Lee Keeler, art by Kenny Keil
  • Apocalyticals: The Worst Generation by John McNamee, art by Elan' Trinidad
  • So We're a Being of Pure Energy, Now What? by Sam Weller
  • Ameripocalypse III by Geoffrey Golden, feat. Paul Scheer, photos by Lynne Donahue
  • The End of the World as Experienced by Cockroaches by Todd Alcott
  • Contributors
  • Oh, the Flesh You Will Eat! by Mike Levine, art by Jacob Vollum
name: Apocalypse
In the Service of the Sun

description:
The people of sylvan Elves are in the place of honor in the second volume in the event series Elfes.

The town of Eysine is under siege by Orc mercenaries. The situation is dire. The kings daughter, against everyones advice, decides to ask the Sylvan Elves for help. Chased by the Orcs, she delves deeper into the forest and finds refuge in a sanctuary preserved by the Elves. The ancient power that haunts the place will recognize the young woman as the last druid descendant What could have saved her people will be, for her, the worst of curses !
name: L'Honneur des Elfes sylvains
